1. Purpose

Define a unified financial architecture for the Meridian ecosystem.

The framework shall:

* Provide deterministic ecosystem-wide costing.
* Support traceability from ecosystem level to individual components.
* Enable event-sourced auditability.
* Establish the Cost Breakdown Structure (CBS) as the authoritative financial namespace.
* Eliminate manual financial aggregation.
* Enforce financial integrity through machine validation and CI governance.

⸻

2. Design Assumptions

2.1 Reference Tier Requirement

All Meridian assets shall be designed and evaluated against pinnacle Tier-0 objectives.

Scenario costing is excluded.

The system shall not model:

* Economy
* Standard
* Premium

variants.

Financial governance focuses on:

* accuracy
* completeness
* traceability
* confidence
* lifecycle exposure

rather than specification trade-offs.

⸻

